# General Coding Standards

## Code Quality

- Write clear, descriptive variable and function names
- Add JSDoc comments for exported functions and classes
- Keep functions focused on a single responsibility
- Use modern JavaScript features (ES6+)

## File Organization

- Group related components and utilities together
- Use index.js for clean exports

## Error Handling

```javascript
// ❌ BAD - Silent failures
try {
  await fetchData();
} catch (e) {}

// ✅ GOOD - Log and handle errors
try {
  await fetchData();
} catch (error) {
  console.error('Failed to fetch data:', error);
  throw new Error('Unable to retrieve data', { cause: error });
}
```


## Accessibility

- Always include appropriate ARIA attributes
- Ensure keyboard navigation works
